#. type: YAML Front Matter: title
#: _posts/2022-04-20-solving-problems-with-extensions.adoc
#, fuzzy, no-wrap
msgid "Solving problems with Quarkus extensions (1/n)"
msgstr "用Quarkus扩展来解决问题（1/n）。"

#. type: YAML Front Matter: synopsis
#: _posts/2022-04-20-solving-problems-with-extensions.adoc
#, fuzzy, no-wrap
msgid ""
"The unique build infrastructure of Quarkus allows you to solve complex "
"issues in a very simple way by developing custom extensions."
msgstr "Quarkus独特的构建基础设施允许你通过开发自定义扩展，以非常简单的方式解决复杂问题。"

#. type: Plain text
#: _posts/2022-04-20-solving-problems-with-extensions.adoc
#, fuzzy
msgid ""
"This is the first post of what I hope will be a series of several articles "
"showing how you can solve complex problems by leveraging the unique Quarkus "
"build infrastructure and extension framework."
msgstr "这是第一篇文章，我希望这将是一系列的文章，展示你如何利用独特的Quarkus构建基础设施和扩展框架来解决复杂的问题。"

#: _posts/2022-04-20-solving-problems-with-extensions.adoc
#, fuzzy
msgid ""
"First things first, bootstraping a Quarkus extension is easy: in one "
"command, you can get it scaffolded and get started on the actual "
"implementation.\n"
"But that's not the subject of this post!"
msgstr "首先，Quarkus 扩展的引导非常简单：只需一条命令，你就可以为它搭建脚手架，并开始实际实施。但这不是本篇文章的主题！"

#: _posts/2022-04-20-solving-problems-with-extensions.adoc
#, fuzzy
msgid ""
"An extension, apart from providing some runtime code to your application, "
"also allows to tweak the build of your application and do all sorts of "
"things at the build level.\n"
"This is what we will focus on in this series."
msgstr "扩展除了为应用程序提供一些运行时代码外，还可以调整应用程序的构建，并在构建级别上做各种事情。这就是我们本系列将重点讨论的内容。"

#: _posts/2022-04-20-solving-problems-with-extensions.adoc
#, fuzzy
msgid ""
"**Problem of the day:** to ensure binary compatibility, the Hub4j GitHub API "
"introduces some bridge methods that confuse Mockito and more specifically "
"ByteBuddy and ultimately make our tests unreliable. How can we solve that?"
msgstr ""
"*今日问题：* 为了确保二进制兼容性，Hub4j GitHub API 引入了一些桥接方法，这些方法会混淆 Mockito，特别是 "
"ByteBuddy，最终导致我们的测试不可靠。我们该如何解决这个问题呢？"

#. type: Title ==
#: _posts/2022-04-20-solving-problems-with-extensions.adoc
#, fuzzy, no-wrap
msgid "Some context"
msgstr "一些背景"

#: _posts/2022-04-20-solving-problems-with-extensions.adoc
#, fuzzy
msgid ""
"You might have heard about https://github.com/quarkiverse/quarkus-github-"
"app[my Quarkus GitHub App extension]\n"
"that allows you to develop GitHub Apps based on Quarkus at light speed with "
"very little boilerplate\n"
"(shameless ad: it is awesome!)."
msgstr ""
"你可能听说过 link:https://github.com/quarkiverse/quarkus-github-app[我的 Quarkus "
"GitHub 应用程序扩展] ，它能让你以极快的速度，只用很少的模板就开发出基于 Quarkus 的 GitHub 应用程序（无耻的广告：它棒极了！）。"

#: _posts/2022-04-20-solving-problems-with-extensions.adoc
#, fuzzy
msgid ""
"My dear colleague https://github.com/yrodiere[Yoann Rodière] (he is awesome "
"too!) wrote some test infrastructure for it based on https://site.mockito."
"org[Mockito]\n"
"(which uses https://bytebuddy.net/[ByteBuddy] under the hood).\n"
"That was all good until we started noticing confusing and non reproducible "
"failures in our tests\n"
"with Mockito sometimes not actually calling the method we would expect."
msgstr ""
"我亲爱的同事 link:https://github.com/yrodiere[Yoann Rodière] （他也很棒！）基于 link:https:/"
"/site.mockito.org[Mockito] （在引擎盖下使用 link:https://bytebuddy.net/[ByteBuddy] "
"）为其编写了一些测试基础架构。这一切都很顺利，直到我们开始注意到测试中出现了令人困惑和不可重现的故障，Mockito "
"有时实际上并没有调用我们期望的方法。"

#. type: Plain text
#: _posts/2022-04-20-solving-problems-with-extensions.adoc
#, fuzzy
msgid ""
"The source of the problem is that, to ensure binary compatibility, the https:"
"//github.com/hub4j/github-api[Hub4j GitHub API] we use in Quarkus GitHub App "
"introduces bridge methods in the bytecode."
msgstr ""
"问题的根源在于，为了确保二进制兼容，我们在Quarkus GitHub App中使用的 link:https://github.com/hub4j/"
"github-api[Hub4j GitHub API] 在字节码中引入了桥接方法。"

#. type: Plain text
#: _posts/2022-04-20-solving-problems-with-extensions.adoc
#, fuzzy
msgid ""
"For instance, let's take this method of the `GitHub` class of the GitHub API:"
""
msgstr "例如，让我们以GitHub API的 `GitHub` 类的这个方法为例。"

#: _posts/2022-04-20-solving-problems-with-extensions.adoc
#, fuzzy
msgid ""
"Historically, it used to return a `GHUser` but, in newer versions, it "
"returns a `GHMyself`,\n"
"which broke the binary compatibility."
msgstr "历史上，它曾返回 `GHUser` ，但在新版本中，它返回 `GHMyself` ，这破坏了二进制兼容性。"

#: _posts/2022-04-20-solving-problems-with-extensions.adoc
#, fuzzy
msgid ""
"To restore it and with the help of the `@WithBridgeMethods` annotation, the "
"GitHub API build will create two methods in the bytecode:\n"
"one returning `GHMyself` and one returning `GHUser`.\n"
"This is very useful if you have compiled your application with an old "
"version of the GitHub API and you just want to use the new version without "
"recompiling your application.\n"
"Typically, in the case of Jenkins, you can switch to a new version of the "
"GitHub API without having to recompile all the Jenkins plugins using GitHub "
"API."
msgstr ""
"为了还原它，在 `@WithBridgeMethods` 注解的帮助下，GitHub API 编译会在字节码中创建两个方法：一个返回 "
"`GHMyself` ，一个返回 `GHUser` 。如果您使用旧版本的 GitHub API 编译了应用程序，而您只想使用新版本的 GitHub "
"API 而无需重新编译应用程序，那么这将非常有用。通常情况下，就 Jenkins 而言，你可以切换到新版本的 GitHub "
"API，而无需重新编译所有使用 GitHub API 的 Jenkins 插件。"

#. type: Plain text
#: _posts/2022-04-20-solving-problems-with-extensions.adoc
#, fuzzy
msgid ""
"At the bytecode level, you end up with something equivalent to the following:"
""
msgstr "在字节码层面，你最终会得到相当于以下的东西。"

#. type: Plain text
#: _posts/2022-04-20-solving-problems-with-extensions.adoc
#, fuzzy
msgid "`invokevirtual` of `getMyself()` that returns `GHMyself`"
msgstr " `invokevirtual` 的 ，返回 `getMyself()` `GHMyself` "

#. type: Plain text
#: _posts/2022-04-20-solving-problems-with-extensions.adoc
#, fuzzy
msgid ""
"And if your existing compiled code calls `GHUser getMyself()`, it will still "
"work after the change of return type."
msgstr "而如果你现有的编译代码调用 `GHUser getMyself()` ，在改变返回类型后，它仍然可以工作。"

#: _posts/2022-04-20-solving-problems-with-extensions.adoc
#, fuzzy
msgid ""
"This bridge methods approach solves a real problem and it's not that big of "
"a deal as it's fully transparent for the developer...\n"
"except when you start using Mockito due to https://github.com/raphw/byte-"
"buddy/issues/1162[a ByteBuddy issue]:\n"
"ByteBuddy can get confused if there are several methods with the same "
"signature but different return types."
msgstr ""
"这种桥接方法解决了一个实际问题，而且它对开发人员来说完全透明，因此并不是什么大问题......除非您由于 link:https://github.com/"
"raphw/byte-buddy/issues/1162[ByteBuddy 问题] 而开始使用 "
"Mockito：如果有几个签名相同但返回类型不同的方法，ByteBuddy 可能会感到困惑。"

#: _posts/2022-04-20-solving-problems-with-extensions.adoc
#, fuzzy
msgid ""
"ByteBuddy is an amazing library and this blog post should not be seen as a "
"critique of ByteBuddy.\n"
"This is an extreme corner case that doesn't happen with standard bytecode."
msgstr "ByteBuddy 是一个了不起的库，这篇博文不应被视为对 ByteBuddy 的批评。这是标准字节码不会出现的极端情况。"

#. type: Plain text
#: _posts/2022-04-20-solving-problems-with-extensions.adoc
#, fuzzy
msgid ""
"This issue was causing our tests to be unreliable because sometimes "
"ByteBuddy was choosing the wrong method to apply Mockito magic."
msgstr "这个问题导致我们的测试不可靠，因为有时ByteBuddy会选择错误的方法来应用Mockito的魔法。"

#. type: Title ==
#: _posts/2022-04-20-solving-problems-with-extensions.adoc
#, fuzzy, no-wrap
msgid "How can we work around this?"
msgstr "我们如何才能解决这个问题？"

#: _posts/2022-04-20-solving-problems-with-extensions.adoc
#, fuzzy
msgid ""
"In the case of Quarkus GitHub App, we don't really care about binary "
"compatibility:\n"
"when upgrading to a new version of the GitHub API,\n"
"users will rebuild their application."
msgstr ""
"就 Quarkus GitHub 应用程序而言，我们并不真正关心二进制兼容性：当升级到新版本的 GitHub API 时，用户将重建他们的应用程序。"

#: _posts/2022-04-20-solving-problems-with-extensions.adoc
#, fuzzy
msgid ""
"So given these bridge methods are problematic,\n"
"one solution would be to get rid of them."
msgstr "因此，鉴于这些桥接方法存在问题，一种解决办法就是取消它们。"

#. type: Plain text
#: _posts/2022-04-20-solving-problems-with-extensions.adoc
#, fuzzy
msgid ""
"Obviously, we could fork the GitHub API and avoid generating the bridge "
"methods."
msgstr "很明显，我们可以分叉GitHub的API，避免生成桥接方法。"

#: _posts/2022-04-20-solving-problems-with-extensions.adoc
#, fuzzy
msgid ""
"But forking and maintaining a fork forever is definitely not something we "
"should consider if we can avoid it.\n"
"Especially since we want to continue benefiting from all the future "
"improvements of the GitHub API."
msgstr "但如果可以避免的话，我们绝对不应该考虑分叉并永远维护一个分叉。尤其是我们希望继续受益于 GitHub API 未来的所有改进。"

#. type: Plain text
#: _posts/2022-04-20-solving-problems-with-extensions.adoc
#, fuzzy
msgid ""
"So could we somehow keep the library standard but have Quarkus adjust the "
"bytecode when building the application?"
msgstr "那么我们是否可以以某种方式保持库的标准，但在构建应用程序时让Quarkus调整字节码？"

#: _posts/2022-04-20-solving-problems-with-extensions.adoc
#, fuzzy
msgid ""
"If you are in a rush, the short answer is yes.\n"
"Now let's go for the (not so) long answer."
msgstr "如果您赶时间，简短的回答是 \"是\"。现在我们来看看（不那么）长的答案。"

